On factory farms that supply McDonaldâ€™s, tens of thousands of birds live in one single barn.
The sheds are kept dark, oftenwith no natural light, which discourages birds from moving.
Birds are tightly packed together and can struggle to even reach food and water.
The air is full of ammonia from their waste. These fumes can burn their throats as they breathe them in.
